      "writtenOn": "2020-07-10T00:39:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see, as we have already reserved 256 bytes for uniform, how about create a constant variable (e.g. kMaxUniformSize \u003d 30) and use a while loop to create shaders in which the size of each shader is a random byte % kMaxUniformSize, and then only one shaders that will be used to be painted and remaining are assgined as its children. \n\nreserve bytes for 1 shader\nwhile (has enough bytes) {\n    size \u003d read a random type % kMaxUniformSize;\n    uniformBytes \u003d read bytes with size size\n    create a shader with uniformBytes and put into children[]\n}\ncreate the shader with children[]",
